title: Google\Cloud\Bigtable\V2\Column
name: Column
description:
Specifies (some of) the contents of a single row/column intersection of a table.

Generated from protobuf message google.bigtable.v2.Column

params.name: data.qualifier
params.description: The unique key which identifies this column within its family. This is the same key that's used to identify the column in, for example, a RowFilter which sets its column_qualifier_regex_filter field. May contain any byte string, including the empty string, up to 16kiB in length.

params.description: Must not be empty. Sorted in order of decreasing "timestamp_micros".
